    "## Synthetic Mode Generation\n",
    "\n",
    "This notebook shows how modes can be elaborated from health states in an fmdtools model."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 1,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import sys, os\n",
    "sys.path.insert(1,os.path.join(\"..\", \"..\"))\n",
    "\n",
    "from fmdtools.modeldef import *\n",
    "import fmdtools.resultdisp as rd\n",
    "import fmdtools.faultsim.propagate as prop\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "import multiprocessing as mp\n",
    "import pandas as pd\n",
    "import time"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "The Rover model is in defined rover_model.py, along with a few analysis methods."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 2,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],

    "from rover_model import Rover, gen_params, plot_map, plot_trajectories, compare_trajectories, plot_course"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Below we compare the space of hazards revealed by querying the model with:\n",
    "   - identifed modes (modes that we identify up-front)\n",
    "   - elaborated modes (modes generated by lists of forseeable parameter values)\n",
    "   - randomly-generated modes (modes generated by randomly sampling ranges of parameter values)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 3,

   "execution_count": 4,
   "metadata": {},

    "fig.savefig(\"rover_structure.pdf\", format=\"pdf\", bbox_inches = 'tight', pad_inches = 0)"
   ]

  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 5,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def plot_hstate_modes(mdl, el_size=10, id_size=30, nom_size=50, el_alpha=1.0, mdl_range=[], range_alpha=1.0, range_size=10, title = \"Space of Fault Modes\"):\n",
    "    x= [hstates.get('friction', 0.0) for mode, hstates in mdl.fxns['Drive'].mode_state_dict.items()  if mode[:5]=='hmode']\n",
    "    y= [hstates.get('transfer', 1.0) for mode, hstates in mdl.fxns['Drive'].mode_state_dict.items()  if mode[:5]=='hmode']\n",
    "    z= [hstates.get('drift', 1.0) for mode, hstates in mdl.fxns['Drive'].mode_state_dict.items()  if mode[:5]=='hmode']\n",
    "    \n",
    "    x_id= [hstates.get('friction', 1.0) for mode, hstates in mdl.fxns['Drive'].mode_state_dict.items() if mode[:5]!='hmode']\n",
    "    y_id= [hstates.get('transfer', 1.0) for mode, hstates in mdl.fxns['Drive'].mode_state_dict.items() if mode[:5]!='hmode']\n",
    "    z_id= [hstates.get('drift', 0.0) for mode, hstates in mdl.fxns['Drive'].mode_state_dict.items() if mode[:5]!='hmode']\n",
    "    id_labels= [mode for mode, hstates in mdl.fxns['Drive'].mode_state_dict.items() if mode[:5]!='hmode']\n",
    "    \n",
    "    fig = plt.figure()\n",
    "    ax = fig.add_subplot(projection='3d')\n",
    "    if mdl_range:\n",
    "        x_r= [hstates.get('friction', 0.0) for mode, hstates in mdl_range.fxns['Drive'].mode_state_dict.items()  if mode[:5]=='hmode']\n",
    "        y_r= [hstates.get('transfer', 1.0) for mode, hstates in mdl_range.fxns['Drive'].mode_state_dict.items()  if mode[:5]=='hmode']\n",
    "        z_r= [hstates.get('drift', 1.0) for mode, hstates in mdl_range.fxns['Drive'].mode_state_dict.items()  if mode[:5]=='hmode']\n",
    "        ax.scatter(x_r, y_r, z_r, label='range', color='yellow', s=range_size, alpha=range_alpha)\n",
    "    \n",
    "    ax.scatter(x, y, z, label='set', color='orange', s=el_size, alpha=el_alpha)\n",
    "    ax.scatter(x_id, y_id, z_id, label='identified', marker='X', color='red', s=id_size, alpha=0.8)\n",
    "    ax.scatter([1.0], [1.0], [0.0], label='nominal', marker='*', color='blue', s=nom_size)\n",
    "    for i, label in enumerate(id_labels):\n",
    "        ax.text(x_id[i], y_id[i], z_id[i], label, ha='left', va='bottom')\n",
    "    ax.set_title(title)\n",
    "\n",
    "    ax.set_xlabel('friction')\n",
    "    ax.set_ylabel('transfer')\n",
    "    ax.set_zlabel('drift')\n",
    "    ax.legend(loc=\"upper left\", framealpha=1)\n",
    "    return fig"
   ]
  },

    "Below we look at how this results in different potential analyses...\n",
    "\n",
    "This function plots the end distribution of a given attribue from the model endclasses."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 8,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def plot_enddist(endclasses, att='line_dist', range=(0,3), endclasses_range=[], density=False, yscale=\"log\", fail_thresh=1.0, thresh_label=\"Off Course\", x_lab=\"Line Distance\", title=\"Results Distributions Given From Approaches\"):\n",
    "    if endclasses_range:\n",
    "        x_range_class = [endclass[att] for scen, endclass in endclasses_range.items() if scen[6:11]=='hmode']\n",
    "        n,bins,patches = plt.hist(x_range_class, density=density, label='range', range=range, color=\"yellow\")\n",
    "        x_elaborated_class = [endclass[att] for scen, endclass in endclasses.items() if scen[6:11]=='hmode']\n",
    "        n,bins,patches = plt.hist(x_elaborated_class, density=density, alpha=0.8, label='set', range=range, bins=bins, color=\"orange\")\n",
    "    else:\n",
    "        x_elaborated_class = [endclass[att] for scen, endclass in endclasses.items() if scen[6:11]=='hmode']\n",
    "        n,bins,patches = plt.hist(x_elaborated_class, density=density, label='set', range=range, color=\"orange\")\n",
    "    \n",
    "    if fail_thresh: plt.axvline(fail_thresh, label=thresh_label, color=\"black\")\n",
    "    \n",
    "    x_identified_class = [endclass[att] for scen, endclass in endclasses.items() if scen[6:11]!='hmode' and scen!='nominal']\n",
    "    label_identified_class = [scen[6:] for scen, endclass in endclasses.items() if scen[6:11]!='hmode'and scen!='nominal']\n",
    "    \n",
    "    _,_,_ = plt.hist(x_identified_class, density=density, alpha=0.8, bins=bins, label='identified', color=\"red\")\n",
    "    plt.grid(axis='y', which='both')\n",
    "    plt.legend()\n",
    "    plt.yscale(yscale)\n",
    "    if yscale==\"log\": plt.ylabel(\"# of Scens (log)\")\n",
    "    else:             plt.ylabel(\"Distribution\")\n",
    "    plt.xlabel(x_lab)\n",
    "    plt.xlim(range)\n",
    "    plt.title(title)\n",
    "    return plt.gcf()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Finding phases so the Approach can inject the fault halfway through the simulation."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 9,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "pool = mp.Pool(4)\n",
    "endresults, resgraph, mdlhist = prop.nominal(mdl_set)\n",
    "phases, modephases = rd.process.modephases(mdlhist)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [

    "\n",
    "We simulate it here to get some idea of the simulation time."
   ]

   "source": [
    "## Cluster Analysis\n",
    "\n",
    "Below, we use clustering to identify similar sets of synthetic modes."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 32,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "from sklearn.cluster import DBSCAN as cluster #DBSCAN"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "To find similar trajectories, we will cluster on the x-y coordinates of the end position of the Rover accross these scenarios:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 33,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "X_range = np.array([[hist['flows']['Ground']['x'][-1],hist['flows']['Ground']['y'][-1]] for scen, hist in mdlhists_range.items() if 'hmode' in scen])\n",
    "ec_range = [endclass['line_dist'] for scen, endclass in endclasses_range.items() if scen[6:11]=='hmode']"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 34,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "X_set = np.array([[hist['flows']['Ground']['x'][-1], hist['flows']['Ground']['y'][-1]] for scen, hist in mdlhists_set.items() if 'hmode' in scen])\n",
    "ec_set = [endclass['line_dist'] for scen, endclass in endclasses_set.items() if scen[6:11]=='hmode']"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 35,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "X_id = np.array([[hist['flows']['Ground']['x'][-1],hist['flows']['Ground']['y'][-1]] for scen, hist in mdlhists_set.items()if 'hmode' not in scen])\n",
    "ec_id = [endclass['line_dist'] for scen, endclass in endclasses_set.items() if scen[6:11]!='hmode' and scen[6:11]!='nominal']"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "To identify where all the clusters are accross al three approaches, we first have to combine the three sets of data into one (otherwise it might cluster differently)."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 43,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "X = np.concatenate((X_range, X_set, X_id))"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "This runs the clustering algorithm:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 44,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "cl = cluster().fit(X)\n",
    "labels = cl.labels_"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "The number of clusters is:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 46,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": [
       "6"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 46,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "unique_labels = set(labels)\n",
    "len(unique_labels)- (1 if -1 in labels else 0)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Here we plot the clusters on the course map to see what the algorithm identified."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 47,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 432x288 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {
      "needs_background": "light"
     },
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "plot_course(mdlhist, label=False)\n",
    "colors = [plt.cm.Spectral(each) for each in np.linspace(0, 1, len(unique_labels))]\n",
    "for k, col in zip(unique_labels, colors):\n",
    "    x_label = [x[0] for i,x in enumerate(X) if labels[i]==k]\n",
    "    y_label = [x[1] for i,x in enumerate(X) if labels[i]==k]\n",
    "    if k == -1: clust_lab = 'unclustered'\n",
    "    else:       clust_lab = 'cluster '+str(k)\n",
    "    plt.scatter(x_label, y_label, label=clust_lab) \n",
    "\n",
    "plt.scatter(X_set[:,0],X_set[:,1], label='set', color='black', marker='+') \n",
    "\n",
    "plt.scatter(X_id[:,0],X_id[:,1], label='identified', color='gray', marker='X')  \n",
    "\n",
    "plt.grid()\n",
    "plt.xlabel('x-distance (m)')\n",
    "plt.ylabel('y-distance (m)')\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.legend()\n",
    "fig = plt.gcf()"
   ]
  },

    "Next, we would like to see how these approaches span the different clusters. If an approach has more coverage, we might say that it better explored the space."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 49,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "categorizations = {tuple(x):labels[i] for i,x in enumerate(X)}"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 50,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [

   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "These are the categories found by each approach:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 53,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": [
       "{-1, 0, 1, 2, 3, 4, 5}"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 53,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "cat_range = [categorizations[tuple(x)] for x in X_range]\n",
    "set(cat_range)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 54,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": [
       "{0, 1, 4}"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 54,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "cat_id = [categorizations[tuple(x)] for x in X_id]\n",
    "set(cat_id)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 55,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": [
       "{-1, 0, 1, 4, 5}"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 55,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "cat_set = [categorizations[tuple(x)] for x in X_set]\n",
    "set(cat_set)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "This function categorizes the results of each approach into the given clusters"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 57,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def get_cats(categorizations, X, ec, unique_categorizations):\n",
    "    cats={}\n",
    "    for cat in unique_categorizations:\n",
    "        cats[cat] = [ec[i] for i,x in enumerate(X) if categorizations[tuple(x)]==cat]+[0]\n",
    "    return cats"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 58,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "cats = get_cats(categorizations,X_range, ec_range, unique_labels)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 59,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def worst_cat(categorizations, X, ec, unique_categorizations):\n",
    "    worst_cats={}\n",
    "    for cat in unique_categorizations:\n",
    "        cats = [ec[i] for i,x in enumerate(X) if categorizations[tuple(x)]==cat]+[0]\n",
    "        worst_cats[cat] = np.max(cats)\n",
    "    return worst_cats"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 60,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "worst_cat_id = worst_cat(categorizations,X_id, ec_id, unique_labels)\n",
    "worst_cat_range = worst_cat(categorizations,X_range, ec_range, unique_labels)\n",
    "worst_cat_set = worst_cat(categorizations,X_set, ec_set, unique_labels)"
   ]
  },

   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Finally, we use the following to calculate more detailed statistics about the cluster coverage."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 100,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def calc_2d_cov_loss(xmin, xmax, ymin, ymax, xs, ys):\n",
    "    return calc_coverage_loss(xmin, xmax, xs)*calc_coverage_loss(ymin, ymax, ys)\n",
    "def calc_coverage_loss(xmin, xmax, xs):\n",
    "    if xs:\n",
    "        return (xmax-np.max(xs)+np.min(xs)-xmin)/(xmax-xmin)\n",
    "    else: \n",
    "        return  (xmax-xmin)/(xmax-xmin)\n",
    "def get_xs_ys(values, X_type):\n",
    "    return [v[0] for v in values if v in X_type], [v[1] for v in values if v in X_type]"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 101,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "cov_loss_id,cov_loss_set,cov_loss_range = [],[],[]\n",
    "num_scens_id,num_scens_set,num_scens_range = [],[],[]\n",
    "for cat, values in cat_values.items():\n",
    "    xs = [v[0] for v in values]\n",
    "    ys = [v[1] for v in values]\n",
    "    xs_id, ys_id = get_xs_ys(values, X_id)\n",
    "    xs_set, ys_set = get_xs_ys(values, X_set)\n",
    "    xs_range, ys_range = get_xs_ys(values, X_range)\n",
    "    xmin,xmax,ymin,ymax = np.min(xs), np.max(xs), np.min(ys), np.max(ys)\n",
    "    \n",
    "    cov_loss_id.append(calc_2d_cov_loss(xmin,xmax,ymin,ymax ,xs_id,ys_id))\n",
    "    cov_loss_set.append(calc_2d_cov_loss(xmin,xmax,ymin,ymax ,xs_set,ys_set))\n",
    "    cov_loss_range.append(calc_2d_cov_loss(xmin,xmax,ymin,ymax, xs_range,ys_range))\n",
    "    \n",
    "    num_scens_id.append(len(xs_id));num_scens_set.append(len(xs_set));num_scens_range.append(len(xs_range))"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [

       "      <td>1.03</td>\n",
       "      <td>1.25</td>\n",

    "pool = mp.Pool(4)\n",
    "def obj_func(x):\n",
    "    x_params = gen_params('sine', ub_f=x[0], lb_f=x[1], ub_t=x[2],lb_t=x[3], ub_d=x[4], lb_d=x[5], cor_f=x[6], cor_d=x[7], cor_t=x[8])\n",
    "    mdl_set = Rover(params=x_params)\n",
    "    app_set = SampleApproach(mdl_set, faults='Drive', phases={'drive':phases['Avionics']['drive']}, defaultsamp={'samp':'evenspacing','numpts':4})\n",
    "    endclasses_set, mdlhists_set = prop.approach(mdl_set, app_set, staged=True, pool=pool)\n",
    "    crash_obj = 1000*sum([ec['line_dist'] for ec in endclasses_set.values() if ec['in_bound']==False])\n",
    "    completion_obj = 10*sum([ec['end_dist'] for ec in endclasses_set.values() if ec['at_finish']==False])\n",
    "    return crash_obj + completion_obj"
   ]

   ]

  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 54,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def plot_mode_contributions(endclasses_opt, mdl):\n",
    "    frictionmodes = [mode for mode, vals in mdl_0.fxns['Drive'].mode_state_dict.items() if vals.get('friction', 1.0)!=1.0]\n",
    "    transfermodes = [mode for mode, vals in mdl_0.fxns['Drive'].mode_state_dict.items() if vals.get('transfer', 1.0)!=1.0]\n",
    "    driftmodes = [mode for mode, vals in mdl_0.fxns['Drive'].mode_state_dict.items() if vals.get('drift', 1.0)!=0.0]\n",
    "    \n",
    "    finish_num_opt_drift = sum([classif['at_finish'] for classif in endclasses_opt.values() if classif['faults']['Drive'][0] in driftmodes])\n",
    "    nofinish_num_opt_drift = sum([not classif['at_finish'] for classif in endclasses_opt.values() if classif['faults']['Drive'][0] in driftmodes])\n",
    "    finish_num_opt_friction = sum([classif['at_finish'] for classif in endclasses_opt.values() if classif['faults']['Drive'][0] in frictionmodes])\n",
    "    nofinish_num_opt_friction = sum([not classif['at_finish'] for classif in endclasses_opt.values() if classif['faults']['Drive'][0] in frictionmodes])\n",
    "    finish_num_opt_transfer = sum([classif['at_finish'] for classif in endclasses_opt.values() if classif['faults']['Drive'][0] in transfermodes])\n",
    "    nofinish_num_opt_transfer = sum([not classif['at_finish'] for classif in endclasses_opt.values() if classif['faults']['Drive'][0] in transfermodes])\n",
    "    fig1, ax1 = plt.subplots()\n",
    "    ax1.pie([finish_num_opt_drift, finish_num_opt_friction, finish_num_opt_transfer, nofinish_num_opt_drift, nofinish_num_opt_friction, nofinish_num_opt_transfer], labels=[\"Drift-Finished\", \"Friction-Finished\", \"Transfer-Finished\",\"Drift-Not Finished\", \"Friction-Not Finished\", \"Transfer-Not Finished\"], autopct='%1.1f%%', startangle=90)\n",
    "    return fig1"
   ]
  },
  {

   "execution_count": 55,
